                            <comment id="13447883" author="cheolsoo" created="Tue, 4 Sep 2012 19:17:41 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I will do this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13448402" author="cheolsoo" created="Wed, 5 Sep 2012 03:30:02 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I added the following text to the REPLACE doc:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Note that the REPLACE function is internally implemented using &lt;a href=&quot;http://docs.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/lang/String.html#replaceAll(java.lang.String, java.lang.String)&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;java.string.replaceAll(String regex, String replacement)&lt;/a&gt; where &apos;regExp&apos; and &apos;newChar&apos; are passed as the 1st and 2nd argument respectively. If you want to replace &lt;a href=&quot;http://docs.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/util/regex/Pattern.html#bs&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;special characters&lt;/a&gt; such as &apos;[&apos; in the string literal, it is necessary to escape them in &apos;regExp&apos; by prefixing them with double backslashes.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13448480" author="billgraham" created="Wed, 5 Sep 2012 05:56:01 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, thanks Cheolsoo!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
